Package for constraints.

Class Summary
ActivityConstraint Checks if the PhysicalEntity controls anything.
AND Used for getting logical AND of a set of constraints.
ConBox Some predefined constraints.
ConstraintAdapter This is a base class for a Constraint.
ControlNotParticipant Checks if a controller of this Control is also a participant of the controlled interactions.
Empty Checks if the parameter constraint cannot generate any candidate.
Equality Checks identity of two elements.
Field Checks if an element has or has not a specific value for a field, or the field value of another element.
FieldOfMultiple Checks if generated elements has or has not a specific value for a field, or the field value of another set of generated elements.
IDConstraint Checks if the element has the desired ID.
InputOrOutput Gets input or output participants of a Conversion.
LinkedPE Many times we want to link PhysicalEntities (PE) while traversing a relation.
ModificationChangeConstraint This is a very specialized constraint that checks if two PhysicalEntity of the same EntityReference have differential features, such that we can predict an activity change based on gain or loss of these features.
MultiPathConstraint Logical OR of several PathConstraints.
NOT Negation of a constraint.
OR Logical OR of several constraints.
OtherSide Given Conversion and its one of the participants (at the left or right), traverses to the other participants that are at the other side.
ParticipatesInConv Gets the related Conversion where the PhysicalEntity is input or output, whichever is desired.
ParticipatingPE This constraint is useful when we want traverse Control-Conversion-PE (input or output).
PathConstraint PathConstraint encapsulates PathAccessor of Paxtools.
PEChainsIntersect This constraint checks if two chains of linked physical entities are intersecting or not.
RelatedControl After traversing a PhysicalEntity and the Conversion it participates, this constraint takes us to the Control.
SelfOrThis When a constraint excludes the origin element, but it is needed to be among them, use this constraint.
Size Checks the size of the generated elements of the wrapped constraint.
Type Checks if a variable is a specific type or its subclass.

Package org.biopax.paxtools.pattern.constraint Description

Package for constraints. ConBox is a special class, not a constraint, but has static methods for creation of frequently used constraints.
